 Graaff-Reinet - A 42-year old woman is expected in court on Monday after she was arrested by Graaff-Reinet police for the alleged murder of a 32-year-old man over the weekend. "It is alleged that the man was stabbed on Saturday, at about 11:45, at Tulip Street, Asherville, Graaff-Reinet," said police spokesperson, Captain Bradley Rawlinson. "The deceased suffered a stab wound to the upper chest. "The motive behind the murder is not known." Capt Rawlinson added that the 42-year-old woman was later arrested . "The suspect is due to appear before Graaff-Reinet Magistrate's Court on Monday." Capt Rawlinson said that the particulars of the deceased cannot be released as his family have not been informed. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 